text:
Okay someone has got to tell her to stop shooting Vergil already lol, I don't know how many times he has to deflect her shots before she realizes the sword which does far more damage is the only way to go against him. Guns are only viable when Vergil is in DT and you have no DT, so you can negate his health regen. Battle 1 is an easy fight, battle 3 is a hard fight, battle 2 is just a really satisfying fight. Here's some important things to remember:

-When Vergil teleports wait until you see him in mid-air before you dash, then close the gap with a stinger.
-When you hear "you're going down" rush him immediately, vorpal blade can be interrupted.
-If you have DT when he has DT rush him and wail on him, it will deplete his DT gauge much quicker.
-If you don't have DT when he has DT do NOT rush him, he has superarmor and will not be staggered by your attacks.
